spanGrp.span: Jiska ra pekaga damĩu tebeli_yaga inga
Je të repoyo wö nẽ damĩ
On the way he saw a duck in front of him;
tara mãĩ pekaga damĩ ñala të sũã'-ra pato damĩu ñala wötsõ
Then he drove toward the side of the road;
ñerö jie të tebeli_yaga tuwã'u-mĩ í kagrei mẽ
Ta ñẽ repoyo wö janã-mĩ e-gla wö
The sheep began to kick it as if it were a ball.
Ñerö í gugá-wã'-ite (m) bola tiö bi klö wa
Then the other sheep found it OK to play with the cabbage;
Ñerö í siga-wa obejo-wa tsõ je káu-mĩ í wö nã (_) pá tã'ĩ Kai jinõ je repoyo wö wa
so they made a goal frame.
Ñerö í të kancha yuá-ra-ite obejo-wa ra je obejo-wa (_)
Then the sheep did not play;
kicked the cabbage and one of them kicked it bang!
Të repoyo wö tiá ñerö e-gla obejo të repoyo tiá ¡pá
It went into the owner’s house, breaking the window.
Kawáu-nẽ í wakwa jũ nã (_) bentana bidrio kwá-wã
So they hid behind a tree.
Ñerö í ña blá-ka-wã kal dleiga
That one sent one of them [to get the ball];
It seems the owners were not home.
Ñerö sela ka í wakwa kuna jũ nã
So he kicked the cabbage back and it broke another window
Ta obejo të repoyo wö tiá klö wa pajá-te otro bidrio kwá-wã-nẽ
and they kept playing with the cabbage.
Ñerö í sigieron jinõ ñẽ repoyo wa
The the pigs were locked in by the side.
Ñerö… ñerö í (_) kagrei mẽ kuchi-wa tabardugá-nẽ wötë-lë wakwa të
The pigs jumped up and down;
je wa kuchi e-gla tur-gẽ ¡pis pis pis
they asked the sheep for the cabbage to eat it.
Je rö (_) obejo-wa ĩã í të repoyo kie-gẽ-ite kete-wã-ra-ite
The sheep teased them with and kept playing;
Ñerö kable-wa të í wöyue-mĩ (_) kable-wa të í wöyue-mĩ ñerö obejo-wa jatanã' jinõ
a small sheep kicked it bang!
Ñerö mãĩ obe obejo e-gla ti/ objejo (m) yuliski të í tiá ¡pá
It went high up in the air,
Ñerö repoyo mẽnẽu siwã inga mẽnẽu siwã
so a pig jumped up and down
ñerö kuchi kuchi mẽnẽu tur-gẽ ¡pis pis je tunã' ¡pis siwã inga
and the sheep ran after it in the air and crashed against each other;
Ñerö obejo mẽnẽu të repoyo kwã' je tunã' ¡pissö ĩã/í töinga (extra) (_) Jie-wa mẽnẽu-lo-mĩ siwã' inga siwã' inga döga komĩ jeska í í kenã'-ra-nã ñã mẽ ta
thus neither the pig nor the sheep could catch the cabbage;
Ñerö ka í të kuchi ni obejo kate repoyo klonẽũ-wã ta
so the cabbage passed by first:
the duck was flying and the cabbage hit him on the tongue.
Je të pato jũr damĩ tiá í köktö (_) inga pajá-mĩ
The duck ate the cabbage and thus could not fly;
Ñerö pato të repoyo katá Despues pato të repoyo katá-wã despues ka í jũr (_) ka í jũr
it could only move its wings knock knock knock!’
të pato pik bö jũr-gẽ ¡plá plá plá plá
